text.__SUMMARY__: Evalea waikikiensis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pyramidellidae, the pyrams and their allies.
text.Description: The white shell has an inflated conical shape. Its length measures 3.1 mm. Its surface is covered with minute striae, that are somewhat more widely spaced.
text.Distribution: This species occurs in the Pacific Ocean off the Hawaiian islands Maui and Oahu.
